This is about distributed systems and how to fail early and often. What Distributed systems:
Leslie Lamport: &ldquo;A distributed system is a system in which a computer that you didn&rsquo;t know existed can render your computer unusable&rdquo;
Why Distributed systems are used when the capacity of a single computer isn&rsquo;t enough to meet our needs. A single computer have finite resources such network bandwidth, compute power, memory and persisten storage.

